result.formatted_address: 90 Hung To Rd, Kwun Tong, Hong Kong
result.name: Corner 90

reviews.text:
I had lunch here today. This is the only Indian restaurant that I know of in Kwun Tong. Had their Indian buffet lunch. The food was quite tasty.

Service was good and the restaurant was full. Price for the lunch was.moderate but reasonable for a buffet

Great Indian food. Loved the chicken and lamb. Great variety of drinks as well. Staff a bit slow and do not always listen to what you want a few times here or there. But most of the time the staff was friendly and great.

Taken over by a chain restaurant group 4 months ago. You know what happened... Beer cost from$68 to $98, food portion shrinks... I have been going there regularly for 8 years. That's it, goodbye. (Changed from 5 stars to 2)

this place is located far from the center in Kwun tong.
the place is a bit expensive but I heard that the buffet is worth it...I ate dinner.
the butter chicken is so tasty and creamy, and the spices are well chosen.
the Dal makhani was so moist and you can sense that it was cooking for hours.
the only downside was that the mango Lassy was finished and miraculously was found after I finished the meal :-(
Indian food was good, the chicken biryani was nothing to write home about.

食物環境都不錯的一間印度餐廳
雖然距離地鐵站有點遠 但也是因為這樣 才可以感受到悠悠閒閒的吃一個午餐
第一次去吃時 覺得價錢有點高 但食物質素是不錯的！
今次去吃時 看到新增了Lunch Buffet ！ 一次過吃到多種口味 值得推薦！
印度人管理的餐廳，對自己的菜式好有自信，保存印度濃郁香氣的味道，份量夠，餐廳環境整潔安靜，不會感到擠迫，適合慢慢品嚐，邊談邊享受美食的地方，推推推👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
食印度嘢唔洗再去尖沙咀啦，餐點選擇多（印式、西式）價格合理，環境舒適，如果要選觀塘十大美味CP值高的食店，我會選她在其中👍🏻
印度式西餐，中午有簡單的印式自助餐，也可以另外單點餐牌的食物，黄昏有happy hour ，交通不算很方便，從官塘站要走來約要8分鐘，隔鄰有酒店，方便遊客。
